Chapter 14: The Scavenger’s Logic
The maintenance shed groaned as the wind outside whipped through the skeletal skyscrapers. Inside, the air was stagnant, smelling of wet concrete and the faint, sweet scent of Void-rot.
Ren sat in the center of the room, the 'Project Architect' folder spread open. Across from him, Mira was trying to fix her staff, but her hands were shaking too hard to hold the crystal steady.
"We can't just stay here, Ren," she whispered. "The Association... they’ll find a way to track the silver light. They always do."
"I'm not staying," Ren said. He closed his eyes, pulling up the System interface.
