Everything has a flaw. You no longer see the surface; you see the 'Degradation Timer'.
Ren opened his eyes. The world looked different. The shed wasn't just a shed anymore. He saw a flickering red number hovering over the support beam: [04:12:21]. In four hours, that beam would fail. He looked at Mira’s staff: [00:58:12].
"Who's there?" Mira suddenly stood, her staff pulsing with a weak, dying light.
A shadow moved at the edge of the shed. Not a monster, but a man. He was draped in heavy, grey rags, with a mechanical respirator mask covering his face. His right arm was a mass of clanking, unpolished iron.
"Old Man Hobs," Ren said, his voice raspy.
The veteran Scavenger stepped into the dim light, his prosthetic arm hissing as the hydraulics adjusted. He looked at Ren, then at the silver-and-black mark on his arm.
"The Zero from the perimeter," Hobs said, his voice a gravelly rumble through the mask. "I told you to watch the reflections, kid. Seems you did more than watch. You jumped in."
"The Association says you're a madman," Mira said, her voice cautious.
"The Association says the sky is blue because they haven't seen it turn purple yet," Hobs grunted. He tossed a heavy, dented metal canister onto the floor. "Drink. It’s Essence-scrubbed. It’ll stop the shaking."
Ren took a sip of the bitter, cold liquid. The 'System' in his mind hummed in approval.
"You knew," Ren said, looking at Hobs. "In Sector 7. You knew the Veil was inhaling."
"I’ve been cleaning up their 'Grade 1' messes for thirty years," Hobs said, sitting on a rusted crate. "I’ve seen students go into the Gates and come out... different. Faster. Stronger. But their shadows always stay behind. You’re the first one I’ve seen who brought his shadow back with him."
Hobs leaned forward, his mechanical eye whirring as it focused on Ren. "You want to defuse the school? You’re going to need more than a glitched blade. The Academy isn't just a bomb, Ren. It’s a 'Null-Point'. It’s holding the weight of the whole city. If you just 'delete' the detonator, the city falls into the Void anyway."
"Then what do I do?"
"You don't defuse it," Hobs said, a grim smile hidden behind his mask. "You 'Refactor' it. You change the foundation. But to do that, you need the 'Black Box'—the original source code the Association used to build the school's core. And there’s only one place it’s kept."
"The Warden’s office," Ren muttered.
"Worse," Hobs replied. "The 'Sub-Vault' beneath the Dormant Gate. The place Silas told you not to look."
