"I have to go back," Ren said, looking at Mira.
"We have to go back," Mira corrected him, her voice finally steady. She looked at her staff, then at Ren. "I’m not going to be 'Data' in their cage anymore."
Ren looked at the 'Entropy Sight' timer on the shed's wall. [03:59:58].
"Hobs, can you get us back in?"
The old man stood up, his iron arm clanking. "I know a way that doesn't involve the front gate. But it’s a crawl through the 'Gut'—the place where the school's waste goes. Are you ready to get your hands dirty, Architect?"
Ren stood up, the black mark on his arm pulsing with a cold, determined light.
"Let's go."
